Mouse & Keyboard                                                      Thing
@line 1 75 0 0 7

@{U}Overview of mouse actions@{u}

@{B} Left drag:@{b}
 ù Objects - Drag&Drop
 ù Desktop or window backgrounds - 'rubber band' selection

@{B} Alternate  + Left drag:@{b}
 ù Drag&Drop with renaming

@{B} Control  + Left drag:@{b}
 ù Drag&Drop with Move (delete originals)

@{B} Left Shift  + Left drag:@{b}
 ù Drag&Drop with creation of symbolic links

@{B} Right Shift  + Left drag:@{b}
 ù Drag&Drop with following of symbolic links

@{B} Left click:@{b}
 ù Object - individual selection 
 ù Window backgrounds - top window
 ù Desktop @{0U}background@{u} - top Thing (MagiC and N.AES only)

@{B} Control  + left click:@{b}
 ù Display context menu

@{B} Shift  + left click:@{b}
 ù Object - additional selections
 ù Window 'Closer' - close window without changing to any parent directory

@{B} Double left click:@{b}
 ù Open object

@{B} Control  + double left click:@{b}
 ù Show file

@{B} Shift  + double left click:@{b}
 ù Start programs in Single mode, if Thing is running as a Shell under 
   MagiC and the program is not an installed application
 ù Open drives or folders in the active directory window

@{B} Alternate  + double left click:@{b}
 ù Open directory to source of desktop icon or group object
 ù Open new window 'relative' to existing folder

@{B} Left double-click and hold:@{b}
 ù 'Real time' scrolling of windows (for single-button mouse users) 

@{B} Right click:@{b}
 ù Top window, if background operation is activated and window is not 
   at the front (topped)
 ù 'Double-click simulation' (with all 'special' non-character keys too) if
   the corresponding option in the 'Desktop' page of the 'Configuration' 
   dialog is active; if not, display the context menu

@{B} Right drag:@{b}
 ù 'Real time' window scrolling in desktop windows

@{B} Right double-click and hold:@{b}
 ù 'Real time scrolling in background windows if 'Background window 
   selection' is not active


@{U}Overview of keyboard actions@{u}

@{B} Alternate  +  A @{b} to @{B} Alternate  +  Z :@{b}
 ù Opens the corresponding drive (A to Z), where available
   Together with  Shift  opens a drive into the active directory window, 
   if available
 ù Selection of the corresponding shortcuts in a dialog field

@{B} Return :@{b}
 ù Open selected object

@{B} Shift  +  Return :@{b}
 ù Start selected program in Single mode, if Thing is running as a 
   Shell under MagiC and the program is not an installed application
 ù Open selected drive or folder in active directory window

@{B} Control  +  Return :@{b}
 ù Display selected file

@{B} Esc :@{b}
 ù Re-read active directory window

@{B} Shift  +  Esc :@{b}
 ù Force media change of active drive
 ù Abandon changes to active object group

@{B} Insert :@{b}
 ù Turn cursor in active directory or group window on/off

@{B} Shift  +  Alternate  +  > :@{b}
 ù Send VA_START to an application named "START" if it is running; 
   normally this is StartMeUp and causes the popup to open. The shortcut 
   can be changed in THINGTXT.RSC.

@{B} Control  +  Backspace :@{b}
 ù Open the 'parent popup' if a directory window is topped and no root 
   directory is being displayed
 
